[04/21/94 public]
The keyseed entered by the user is neither a password nor a key.  
It is a string that is combined with a timestamp to
generate a temporary DES key which is used to "seed" a random
key generator that is used to generate a random
"master key."  The "master key" is the key (stored in the
/opt/dcelocal/var/security/.mkey file) used to encrypt the
rgy database account keys.  The "master key" is also used
to re-initialize the random key generator used to generate
random keys (e.g., for server accounts via ktadd -r).

